Project Title: Portfolio Website Design
Objective
To create a visually appealing and user-friendly portfolio website that showcases your work, skills, and achievements. This project will help you demonstrate your creativity, design skills, and ability to build a functional website.

Project Goals
Showcase Your Work: Highlight your best projects with detailed descriptions, images, and links.
Present Your Skills: Provide a clear overview of your skills and expertise.
Introduce Yourself: Include an engaging bio and a professional photo.
Facilitate Contact: Make it easy for potential employers or clients to contact you.
Project Requirements
Homepage

Brief introduction and overview of the website.
Navigation bar with links to different sections (About, Projects, Contact).
About Page

A short bio about yourself, your background, and your interests.
A professional photo.
A section detailing your skills and experience.
Projects Page

A gallery of your best projects.
Each project should include:
Project title.
Description of the project.
Technologies used.
Images or screenshots.
Links to live projects or repositories (if available).
Contact Page

Contact form for visitors to get in touch with you.
Your email address and links to your social media profiles.
Design Considerations
User Experience (UX)

Ensure the website is easy to navigate.
Use a clean and intuitive layout.
Visual Design

Choose a consistent color scheme and typography.
Use high-quality images and graphics.
Ensure that the design reflects your personal brand and style.
Responsiveness

Ensure the website is mobile-friendly and works well on different devices and screen sizes.
Performance

Optimize images and other media for fast loading times.
Use efficient coding practices to ensure the website runs smoothly.
Technologies
HTML/CSS/JavaScript: For building the structure, styling, and interactivity of the website.
Frameworks/Libraries (Optional):
Bootstrap or Tailwind CSS for responsive design.
jQuery or other JavaScript libraries for additional functionality.
Content Management Systems (Optional):
WordPress or Webflow if you prefer not to code everything from scratch.
Deliverables
Design Mockups

Wireframes or mockups of the website layout (using tools like Figma, Sketch, or Adobe XD).
Website Files

HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files.
Any images or media used in the project.
